citation.case_name: Gulf-Canal Lines, Inc. v. United States

html:
386 U.S. 348

87 S.Ct. 1161

18 L.Ed.2d 98

GULF-CANAL LINES, INC., et al.
v.
UNITED STATES et al.

No. 947.

Supreme Court of the United States

March 20, 1967

Harry C. Ames, Jr., T. Randolph Buck, Nuel D. Belnap and Richard J. Hardy, for appellants.

Solicitor General Marshall, Assistant Attorney General Turner, Howard E. Shapiro, Robert W. Ginnane and Fritz R. Kahn, for the United States and others.

Nuel D. Belnap and Richard J. Hardy, for Waterways Freight Bureau, amicus curiae.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to affirm is granted and the judgment is affirmed.
